        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Spartanburg, or 4 miles east of USC Upstate,
moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Spartanburg, Boiling Springs SC, Cowpens, USC Upstate, Croft State
Park, Cedar Springs, and Mayo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
